ish: habitational name from either of two places, in Cheshire and Yorkshire, called Ledsham. The first is named with the Old English personal name <i>Lēofede</i> + Old English <i>hām</i> ‘homestead’ and the second is recorded in Domesday Book as <i>Ledesham</i> ‘homestead within the district of Leeds’."]},{"name":"Ledsom","meanings":["English:  see  Ledsham  ."]},{"name":"Ledson","meanings":["1  English: principally a variant of   Ledsham  .","2  English: locative name, occasionally perhaps from Ledston (WR Yorks) with loss of  <i>-t-</i>.","3  English:  see  Letson  ."]},{"name":"Ledsam","meanings":["English:  see  Ledsham  ."]},{"name":"Leadsom","meanings":["English:  see  Ledsham  ."]}]},{"name":"Susanna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Suzannah","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."]},{"name":"Suzanna","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."]},{"name":"Susana","meanings":["From Hebrew.  See  <b>Susanna</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Susanna Ledsham was born in 1464, in Crewe, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Roger Ledsham , Gentleman of Chester, was 21 and her mother, Lady Joan Alice, was 19. She married Sir William Sneyd in 1485, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 14 February 1538, in Frodesley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1464–14 February 1538":"1464–14. veebruar 1538","1464–1538":"1464–1538","1466–1505":"1466–1505","1464–1543":"1464–1543","1462–Male":"1462–Surnud","1486–1538":"1486–1538","1482–Male":"1482–Surn